## Vue 3.5 Props Pattern

Use destructuring props with inline types and defaults instead of interfaces and withDefaults:

**✅ Preferred (Vue 3.5+):**
```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
const {
  variant = 'default',
  size = 'md',
  disabled = false,
  class: className,
} = defineProps<{
  variant?: 'default' | 'primary' | 'secondary'
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg'
  disabled?: boolean
  class?: string
}>()

defineEmits<{
  click: [event: MouseEvent]
}>()
</script>
```

**❌ Avoid (Old pattern):**
```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
interface Props {
  variant?: 'default' | 'primary'
  size?: 'sm' | 'md'
}

const props = withDefaults(defineProps<Props>(), {
  variant: 'default',
  size: 'md',
})
</script>
```

## Key Benefits
- No separate interface needed
- Default values inline with destructuring
- Direct variable access (no `props.` prefix)
- More concise and readable
- Better TypeScript inference